# .gitignore — gomatic Go repository standard
#
# Ignore ONLY the build and test/coverage artifacts the Go toolchain and the
# gomatic/build Makefile produce in a clean checkout. Cross-repo droppings from
# editors, OSes, and AI assistants (.idea/ .vscode/ .cursor/ .claude/ .DS_Store
# node_modules/ …) do NOT belong here — they live once in the global ignore at
# ~/.config/git/ignore so every repo inherits them. Add only genuinely
# app-specific paths for THIS repo below the standard block.

# Build output: `make build` (bin/), `make build-all` / goreleaser (dist/)
/bin/
/dist/

# Test + coverage: `make cover` / `make test-all` (COVERAGE_FOLDER=var),
# compiled test binaries, and stray coverage profiles/reports
/var/
*.test
*.out
/coverage*
